From: Pablo Neira Ayuso <pablo@netfilter.org>
Date: Fri, 22 Sep 2023 18:30:28 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] netfilter: nft_set_hash: try later when GC hits EAGAIN on
 iteration
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 6.1.56
Git-commit: b079155faae94e9b3ab9337e82100a914ebb4e8d

commit b079155faae94e9b3ab9337e82100a914ebb4e8d upstream.

Skip GC run if iterator rewinds to the beginning with EAGAIN, otherwise GC
might collect the same element more than once.

Fixes: f6c383b8c31a ("netfilter: nf_tables: adapt set backend to use GC transaction API")
Signed-off-by: Pablo Neira Ayuso <pablo@netfilter.org>
Signed-off-by: Sasha Levin <sashal@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Robert Frohl <rfrohl@suse.com>
---
 net/netfilter/nft_set_hash.c | 9 +++------
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/net/netfilter/nft_set_hash.c b/net/netfilter/nft_set_hash.c
index eca20dc60138..2013de934cef 100644
--- a/net/netfilter/nft_set_hash.c
+++ b/net/netfilter/nft_set_hash.c
@@ -338,12 +338,9 @@ static void nft_rhash_gc(struct work_struct *work)
 
 	while ((he = rhashtable_walk_next(&hti))) {
 		if (IS_ERR(he)) {
-			if (PTR_ERR(he) != -EAGAIN) {
-				nft_trans_gc_destroy(gc);
-				gc = NULL;
-				goto try_later;
-			}
-			continue;
+			nft_trans_gc_destroy(gc);
+			gc = NULL;
+			goto try_later;
 		}
 
 		/* Ruleset has been updated, try later. */
